---

<PageShell
  title="France Investor & Entrepreneur Visa 2026: Passeport Talent Business Guide"
  description="Complete guide to France's Passeport Talent for entrepreneurs and investors. Business creation (€30,000), economic investment (€300,000+), 4-year visa, family included, path to EU residence."
  headline="France Investor & Entrepreneur Visa: Passeport Talent Guide"
  subheadline="Everything you need to know about France's entrepreneur and investor visas—Passeport Talent options, €30,000-€300,000 requirements, La French Tech ecosystem, and path to permanent residence."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Premium Insurance"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/axa-global"
  heroImage="/images/countries/france-hero-bg.png"
>

  <!-- Trust Signals -->
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-8 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Updated February 2026
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      Official French Requirements
    </span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg>
      4-Year Multi-Year Visa
    </span>
  </div>

  <!-- Section: Overview -->
  <section id="overview" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      France does not offer a traditional "Golden Visa" with passive real estate investment. Instead, it provides entrepreneur and investor pathways through the Passeport Talent program—a multi-year visa designed to attract business creators, significant investors, and company executives to France. These routes require active business involvement rather than passive capital placement.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Passeport Talent offers substantial advantages: a 4-year visa from the start, automatic family inclusion, and access to France's thriving startup ecosystem (La French Tech). For entrepreneurs with innovative projects, the Business Creation track requires just €30,000 in capital—far less than most European investment programs. For larger investors, the Economic Investor track welcomes those deploying €300,000+ into French companies.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts: France Entrepreneur & Investor Visas</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-primary-800">
        <li>• <strong>Main program:</strong> Passeport Talent (multiple categories)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Business Creation:</strong> €30,000 capital + innovative project</li>
        <li>• <strong>Economic Investor:</strong> €300,000+ direct investment</li>
        <li>• <strong>Company Representative:</strong> Establish French branch/subsidiary</li>
        <li>• <strong>Duration:</strong> Up to 4 years (multi-year from start)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Family included:</strong> Spouse and children receive "Passeport Talent - Famille"</li>
        <li>• <strong>Path to PR:</strong> 5 years; citizenship: 5 years</li>
        <li>• <strong>Work rights:</strong> Full work and business rights in France</li>
        <li>• <strong>Schengen access:</strong> Travel freely within 26 Schengen countries</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why Choose France for Business?</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Advantages</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• 4-year visa from the start (no renewals for 4 years)</li>
          <li>• Family included automatically</li>
          <li>• La French Tech ecosystem and startup support</li>
          <li>• Lower capital requirement (€30,000) than most EU programs</li>
          <li>• Access to EU's second-largest economy</li>
          <li>• Excellent quality of life and infrastructure</li>
          <li>• Strong investor incentives and R&D tax credits</li>
          <li>• Gateway to entire EU market</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• Must actively run or invest in business (not passive)</li>
          <li>• French language increasingly expected</li>
          <li>• Complex business regulations and labor laws</li>
          <li>• Higher taxes than some EU countries</li>
          <li>• Business plan must demonstrate innovation/benefit</li>
          <li>• Social charges add to employment costs</li>
          <li>• Bureaucracy can be challenging</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>La French Tech:</strong> France has aggressively positioned itself as Europe's startup capital. La French Tech is a government-backed initiative supporting innovation and entrepreneurship, with dedicated visa tracks, incubators, funding programs, and a growing ecosystem of unicorns. Paris ranks as one of Europe's top three startup hubs alongside London and Berlin.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Quick Decision Guide -->
  <section id="quick-decision" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Quick Decision Guide</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">France's Passeport Talent is Right For You If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• You want to actively build or invest in a business</li>
          <li>• You have an innovative project or startup idea</li>
          <li>• You can commit €30,000+ in capital</li>
          <li>• You want a long-term visa (4 years) from day one</li>
          <li>• You want your family included automatically</li>
          <li>• You're comfortable learning French</li>
          <li>• You want access to the EU market</li>
          <li>• You value startup ecosystem support</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Other Options If:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>• You want passive investment (consider Portugal, Greece)</li>
          <li>• You prefer real estate investment routes</li>
          <li>• You have no business plans—just want residency</li>
          <li>• You need minimal stay requirements</li>
          <li>• You want lower tax environments</li>
          <li>• You're uncomfortable with French bureaucracy</li>
          <li>• You prefer English-only business environment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">France vs. Other EU Business/Investment Options</h3>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Country</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Min. Investment</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Type</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left">Path to Citizenship</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">France (Business Creation)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">€30,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Active business</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">5 years</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-neutral-50">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">France (Economic Investor)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">€300,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Direct investment</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">5 years</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Spain (Golden Visa)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">€500,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Passive (real estate)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">10 years</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-neutral-50">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Portugal (Golden Visa)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">€500,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Funds/capital</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">5 years</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">Germany (Entrepreneur)</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">No minimum</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">Viable business plan</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-2">8 years (6 with integration)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Why France stands out:</strong> France offers the lowest capital requirement (€30,000) among major EU countries for serious entrepreneur visas, combined with a 4-year multi-year permit from the start. Unlike passive golden visas, you must be actively involved, but you gain access to Europe's second-largest economy and a thriving startup ecosystem with substantial government support.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Visa Requirements -->
  <section id="visa-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Visa Requirements</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      France offers several pathways for entrepreneurs and investors under the Passeport Talent umbrella. The Business Creation track is most accessible for startups, while Economic Investor suits those making substantial capital commitments. Each has distinct requirements.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={visaColumns} rows={visaRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Passeport Talent - Business Creation (Création d'Entreprise)</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      This is the primary route for entrepreneurs starting innovative businesses in France. It's designed for founders with projects that will contribute to France's economic development.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Requirements:</h4>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
        <li>• <strong>Capital:</strong> Minimum €30,000 deposited in a French bank account</li>
        <li>• <strong>Business plan:</strong> Detailed plan showing viability and French economic benefit</li>
        <li>• <strong>Innovation:</strong> Project should be innovative or fill market gap</li>
        <li>• <strong>Qualifications:</strong> Master's degree or 5+ years professional experience in relevant field</li>
        <li>• <strong>Business structure:</strong> Establish or control a French company (SAS, SARL, etc.)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Investment use:</strong> Capital must be used for business operations</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Passeport Talent - Economic Investor (Investisseur Économique)</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      For larger investors making direct investments in French companies. This track suits those with significant capital who want to invest in existing businesses or create new ventures with substantial initial funding.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Requirements:</h4>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
        <li>• <strong>Investment:</strong> €300,000+ in tangible or intangible fixed assets</li>
        <li>• <strong>Investment type:</strong> Direct investment in French company (not financial instruments)</li>
        <li>• <strong>Job creation:</strong> Investment should create or preserve jobs</li>
        <li>• <strong>Control:</strong> Hold at least 10% of company capital</li>
        <li>• <strong>Role:</strong> Exercise management or supervisory function in the company</li>
        <li>• <strong>Commitment:</strong> 4-year investment commitment</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Passeport Talent - Company Representative</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      For executives establishing French branches or subsidiaries of foreign companies. Ideal for multinational expansion into the French market.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Key Requirements</h4>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Employed by foreign company for 3+ months, sent to France to establish or manage a branch/subsidiary. Company must demonstrate financial stability and business rationale for French expansion.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Alternative: Entrepreneur/Profession Libérale Visa</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      A simpler but shorter-duration option for those who don't qualify for Passeport Talent. Suitable for smaller-scale entrepreneurs and freelance professionals establishing businesses in France.
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Advantages</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• Lower capital requirements (varies)</li>
          <li>• No innovation requirement</li>
          <li>• Suitable for traditional businesses</li>
          <li>• Path to longer-term residence</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>• Only 1-year initial permit (annual renewals)</li>
          <li>• More scrutiny of business viability</li>
          <li>• Family must apply separately</li>
          <li>• Longer path to stable status</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-amber-800">
        <strong>Important:</strong> France requires a genuine business operation—not just capital parking. Authorities evaluate your business plan, qualifications, and the project's benefit to the French economy. Be prepared to demonstrate that your venture will create value, jobs, or innovation in France.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Insurance Requirements -->
  <section id="insurance-requirements" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">Health Insurance is Mandatory for Visa Application</h3>
      <p class="text-green-800">
        All Passeport Talent applicants must provide proof of comprehensive health insurance covering France. This is required for your visa application and must remain valid throughout your stay. After establishing residence, you can transition to France's public healthcare system (CPAM).
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">
      France has excellent healthcare but requires visa applicants to have private coverage initially. Unlike residents who work and pay social contributions, new arrivals must demonstrate they won't burden the public system. Once you're legally resident and running your business, you can enroll in the French social security system.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={insuranceColumns} rows={insuranceRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">What Coverage You Need</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Your health insurance policy must meet these requirements for visa approval:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Comprehensive coverage:</strong> Hospitalization, outpatient care, emergency treatment</li>
      <li><strong>Minimum coverage:</strong> €30,000+ (matching Schengen requirements)</li>
      <li><strong>Geographic coverage:</strong> Must explicitly cover France</li>
      <li><strong>Duration:</strong> Minimum 12 months for initial application</li>
      <li><strong>No exclusions:</strong> Policy cannot exclude common medical needs</li>
      <li><strong>Repatriation:</strong> Coverage for medical evacuation/repatriation recommended</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Insurance Options for Entrepreneurs</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-blue-200 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">International Private Insurance</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
          <li>• Worldwide coverage for business travel</li>
          <li>• English-language service</li>
          <li>• Portable if you relocate</li>
          <li>• Often better pre-existing condition coverage</li>
          <li>• Premium hospitals and specialists</li>
          <li>• Higher cost (€200-500/month)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">CFE + Complementary Insurance</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>• Caisse des Francais de l'Etranger option</li>
          <li>• Allows access to French social security rates</li>
          <li>• Lower monthly costs (€100-200)</li>
          <li>• Pairs with mutuelle for full coverage</li>
          <li>• Familiar French system</li>
          <li>• France-focused coverage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Transitioning to French Social Security</h3>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Once you're legally resident in France and operating your business, you can join the French social security system:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>Self-employed (Travailleur Indépendant):</strong> Pay social contributions through URSSAF; gain healthcare access through SSI (Sécurité Sociale des Indépendants)</li>
      <li><strong>Company director (Assimilé salarié):</strong> SAS president with salary pays into general regime; access to CPAM</li>
      <li><strong>Timeline:</strong> Usually 3-6 months after business registration to gain carte vitale</li>
      <li><strong>Keep private insurance:</strong> Many entrepreneurs maintain private coverage alongside for faster access and premium care</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Our recommendation:</strong> Start with international insurance from AXA Global or Cigna Global for your visa application. This provides immediate, comprehensive coverage and works well for the business travel typical of entrepreneurs. After 6-12 months in France, evaluate whether to transition to the French system or maintain private coverage based on your needs and costs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

