  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Passeport Talent application involves preparing your business plan, securing capital, and gathering extensive documentation. Processing typically takes 2-3 months. You can start your business activities immediately upon visa approval—no need to wait for the residence card.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Develop Your Business Plan</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Create a detailed business plan in French (or with French translation). Include market analysis, financial projections, job creation plans, and how your project benefits France. For innovative projects, emphasize technology, intellectual property, or market disruption. This is the most scrutinized part of your application.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Open French Bank Account and Deposit Capital</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Open a business account with a French bank. Some banks (like Qonto, Shine) allow remote opening; traditional banks typically require in-person visits. Deposit your €30,000+ capital and obtain a certificate (attestation de dépôt de fonds). The funds are blocked until company registration.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Register Your Company (Optional at This Stage)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">You can register your company before or after visa approval. Common structures: SAS (simplified joint-stock company—most popular for startups), SARL (limited liability company), or auto-entrepreneur (for smaller operations). Registration is done through the guichet unique (one-stop shop) at INPI.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Arrange Health Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Obtain comprehensive health insurance from an international or French insurer. Get a certificate confirming coverage for France for the full visa duration. This can be done quickly—most insurers provide documentation within 24-48 hours.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Gather Supporting Documents</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Compile: valid passport, passport photos, business plan, proof of capital (bank certificate), health insurance certificate, proof of qualifications (diplomas, CV), proof of address in France (if available), clean criminal record from home country, and completed visa application forms. Documents must be translated into French by sworn translator.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit Visa Application at French Consulate</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Book an appointment at your local French consulate. Submit all documents and pay the €225 visa fee. You may be interviewed about your business plans. Processing typically takes 2-3 months—longer during busy periods or if additional documentation is requested.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">7</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Receive Visa and Travel to France</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Upon approval, your passport is stamped with a long-stay visa (VLS-TS) valid for up to 4 years. This visa acts as your residence permit during the first year. Travel to France within 3 months of visa issuance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">8</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Validate Visa with OFII</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Within 3 months of arrival, validate your visa online through the OFII (French Immigration Office) website. Pay the €200 tax and schedule a medical examination if required. This activates your residence rights and starts the clock toward permanent residence.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">9</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Apply for Residence Card (After Year 1)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Before your first year expires, apply at your local prefecture for the multi-year residence card (carte de séjour pluriannuelle). Provide proof that your business is operating—financial statements, employee records if applicable, social contribution payments. The card is issued for the remaining 3 years of your 4-year authorization.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Family applications:</strong> Your spouse and minor children can apply simultaneously for "Passeport Talent - Famille." They receive the same 4-year authorization and full work rights in France. Each family member needs their own health insurance policy. Submit family applications together for efficiency.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

